    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the trees of the genus Laburnum, having a striking, dark greenish brown or reddish brown color, fine grain, and capable of taking a high polish. It is typically used for cabinetmaking and inlay.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
